might try to come up

00:02:32.040 --> 00:02:36.680
with new updates, new
content, oftentimes the users

00:02:36.680 --> 00:02:40.650
may just not remember and may
not be coming back to your app.

00:02:40.650 --> 00:02:43.800
And app indexing is a good
way to solve this problem.

00:02:43.800 --> 00:02:48.930
So what app indexing does,
it lets you create deep links

00:02:48.930 --> 00:02:52.070
from Google search
into your native app.

00:02:52.070 --> 00:02:56.110
So as you see on an
example on the screen

00:02:56.110 --> 00:02:59.240
there, when I search
for, let's say,

00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:03.140
