00:03:03.140 --> 00:03:05.410
Google search shows
me, hey you can

00:03:05.410 --> 00:03:08.000
view this content in IMDB app.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.050
And when I tap on that I get
deep linked right into the app.

00:03:12.050 --> 00:03:15.330
Now as native app developers
this is particularly important

00:03:15.330 --> 00:03:17.700
because you might have
unique experiences

00:03:17.700 --> 00:03:20.470
in the native environment
that you otherwise would not

00:03:20.470 --> 00:03:22.370
have on your mobile website.

00:03:22.370 --> 00:03:25.130
So app indexing is
really a good way

00:03:25.130 --> 00:03:28.540
to help bring that users from
search, which is typically

00:03:28.540 --> 00:03:31.360
where they start to
look for content,

00:03:31.360 --> 00:03:34.370
and bring that back
into your native app.

00:03:34.370 --> 00:03:36.980
